excerpt: Gleaming titanium and glass museum, designed by Frank Gehry, housing major 20th-century artworks.
detail_description: The Guggenheim Museum Bilbao is a stunning titanium and glass structure designed by Frank Gehry, showcasing major 20th-century artworks. It's located in Bilbao, a city that beautifully blends old and new. The museum is accessible via the unique Zubri Zuri Bridge, which has become an attraction in itself. While visiting, don't miss walking along the River Nervion for breathtaking views of the museum's futuristic architecture.
name: Guggenheim Museum Bilbao
address: Abandoibarra Etorb., 2, Abando, 48009 Bilbao, Bizkaia, Spain

excerpt: Art venue including works by Velázquez, Goya & Picasso & known for its pieces by Basque artists.
detail_description: The Museum of Fine Arts of Bilbao is a renowned art venue that boasts an extensive collection featuring works by prominent artists such as Velázquez, Goya, and Picasso. The museum also showcases pieces by Basque artists, adding a local touch to its exhibits.
name: Museum of Fine Arts of Bilbao
address: Museo Plaza, 2, Abando, 48009 Bilbao, Bizkaia, Spain

excerpt: Casco Viejo forms the medieval old quarter, a lively riverside district with modern shops and traditional taverns lining the Seven Streets. La Ribera market has food stalls in a boatlike waterfront structure, flanked by pintxo bars serving Basque tapas on sticks. Santiago Cathedral is a 14th-century landmark with a dramatic Gothic spire, and Teatro Arriaga draws well-dressed crowds to opera and dance performances.
detail_description: Casco Viejo, also known as the old quarter, is a vibrant district in Bilbao with a mix of modern shops and traditional taverns along the Seven Streets. The area features La Ribera market, where food stalls are housed in a boatlike waterfront structure and pintxo bars serve Basque tapas on sticks. Santiago Cathedral, a 14th-century Gothic landmark, and Teatro Arriaga draw crowds to opera and dance performances.
name: Casco Viejo
address: Ibaiondo, Bilbao, Biscay, Spain

excerpt: Fitness center, cinema, theater, exhibitions & lectures in a Philippe Starck-designed space.
detail_description: Azkuna Zentroa-Alhóndiga Bilbao, located in the Indautxu district, is a cultural and leisure center housed in a former wine warehouse. Designed by Philippe Starck, it offers a variety of amenities such as a fitness center, cinema, theater, exhibitions, and lectures. The modern interior features an indoor swimming pool with a transparent bottom on the fourth floor.
name: Azkuna Zentroa-Alhóndiga Bilbao
address: Arriquíbar Plaza, 4, Abando, 48010 Bilbao, Bizkaia, Spain

excerpt: City center 21-acre park with sweeping lawns, a pond, fountains & pergola, open since 1907.
detail_description: Parque Doña Casilda Iturrizar is a serene 21-acre park located in the heart of Bilbao, offering a peaceful retreat from the urban hustle. Established in 1907, this English-style garden boasts lush lawns, charming ponds with ducks, swans, and peacocks, as well as elegant fountains and a picturesque pergola.
name: Parque Doña Casilda Iturrizar
address: Abando, 48009 Bilbao, Biscay, Spain

detail_description: Estadio de San Mamés, also known as The Cathedral, is a must-visit in Bilbao. It's the largest football stadium in the Basque Country and the 8th largest in Spain. The stadium has received accolades such as the World Design Awards 2020.
name: Estadio de San Mamés
address: P.º Rafael Moreno "Pitxitxi", s/n, Basurtu-Zorrotza, 48013 Bilbao, Bizkaia, Spain

excerpt: Mountain station & viewpoint overlooking Bilbao for funicular railway, open since 1915.
detail_description: Ascend to the top of Mount Artxanda in Bilbao with a ride on the Funicular de Artxanda, which has been operating since 1915. This old-styled, red funicular offers stunning panoramic views over Bilbao's center, including sights like the Guggenheim Museum and the city's river. At the top, a spacious park awaits with sculptures and more viewpoints. The first wagon is ideal for photographers looking to capture unobstructed shots.
name: Funicular de Artxanda
address: Carretera Artxanda-Santo Domingo Errepidea, 27, 48015 Bilbao, Bizkaia, Spain

detail_description: When visiting Bilbao, don't miss the opportunity to experience the iconic Zubizuri Bridge, also known as Campo Volantin Bridge. This pedestrian bridge spans across the picturesque Nervion River and is a must-see attraction in the city. Its unique design and scenic location make it a charming spot for visitors to explore while taking in the beauty of Bilbao.
name: Zubizuri
address: Bilbao, Vizcaya, Spain

detail_description: Old Town by BilbaoLiving is a vibrant area in Bilbao, offering a mix of historical charm and modern attractions. Visitors can explore pedestrianized streets, historical monuments, and over 800 shops selling everything from handicrafts to designer clothes. The district is known for its Basque craft items, including pottery, crystal, leather products, and traditional furniture. Additionally, the Old Town boasts numerous restaurants and bars where visitors can savor local pintxos and wine.
name: Old Town by BilbaoLiving
address: Prim Kalea, 8, 1º izda, Ibaiondo, 48006 Bilbao, Biscay, Spain

excerpt: Pedestrian bridge over the Nervión River with a futuristic tied-arch design & a curved walkway.
detail_description: Zubizuri, also known as the "White Bridge," is a futuristic pedestrian bridge over the Nervión River in Bilbao. Its unique tied-arch design and curved walkway make it a charming addition to the city's modern art and architectural landscape. Designed with a playful touch, the bridge gleams like a majestic swan caught in a snowstorm, adding an element of whimsy to its surroundings.
name: Zubizuri
address: Zubizuri, Abando, 48001 Bilbao, Biscay, Spain

excerpt: Bilbao, an industrial port city in northern Spain, is surrounded by green mountains. It’s the de facto capital of Basque Country, with a skyscraper-filled downtown. It’s famed for the Frank Gehry–designed Guggenheim Museum Bilbao, which sparked revitalization when it opened in 1997. The museum houses prominent modern and contemporary works, but it’s the curvy, titanium-clad building that receives the most attention.
detail_description: Bilbao, a vibrant city in northern Spain, is known for its stunning blend of modern architecture and natural beauty. The iconic Guggenheim Museum Bilbao, designed by Frank Gehry, stands as a symbol of the city's revitalization. Nestled amidst green mountains and overlooking the Bay of Biscay, Bilbao offers a diverse experience for travelers. From surfing along the Atlantic coast to exploring the picturesque towns and fishing villages, there's no shortage of adventure.
name: Bilbao
address: Biscay, Spain

excerpt: Scenic thoroughfare with spacious squares, park benches, statues, boutiques & a department store.
detail_description: Gran Vía de Don Diego López de Haro is a picturesque street lined with wide squares, park benches, and statues. It's also home to various boutiques and a department store. For an authentic experience, visit Arrese, a renowned bakery located at Gran Via 24. Indulge in their oversized truffles filled with cream, chocolate, Baileys or Cointreau, which are available in stylish retro packaging.
name: Gran Vía de Don Diego López de Haro
address: Abando, Bilbao, Bizkaia, Spain

detail_description: Teatro Arriaga, located in Bilbao, Spain, is a renowned neo-baroque opera house named after Basque composer Juan Crisostomo de Arriaga. Built in 1890, it boasts an opulent design and a rich costume collection. The theater offers guided tours in English, Basque, and Spanish for a nominal fee.
name: Arriaga Theater
address: Arriaga Plaza, 1, Ibaiondo, 48005 Bilbao, Bizkaia, Spain

excerpt: Museum about shipbuilding & the city's reinvention of its port in the former Euskalduna shipyard.
detail_description: Located in the former Euskalduna shipyard, Itsasmuseum Bilbao is a unique museum that showcases the city's deep connection with the sea and its maritime history. The museum offers a comprehensive exploration of Bilbao's seafaring traditions and shipbuilding legacy through interactive exhibits, artifacts, and multimedia displays in a modern building along the Nervion River.
name: Itsasmuseum Bilbao
address: Ramón de la Sota Kaia, 1, Abando, 48013 Bilbao, Bizkaia, Spain

detail_description: Moyúa, located in the heart of Bilbao, is a bustling square known as Plaza de Don Federico Moyua. It's a popular spot for tourists and locals alike, offering easy access to various attractions such as the Bilbao Exhibition Center and Haceria Aretoa. The square underwent renovations in 1997, transforming it into a welcoming space adorned with colorful flowers and an elegant fountain, making it a picturesque location for photography enthusiasts.
name: Moyúa
address: Abando, 48011 Bilbao, Bizkaia, Spain

detail_description: Palacio Euskalduna is a remarkable performance and convention center located in the heart of Bilbao. It was built on the site of a former shipyard and designed by renowned architect Frank O. Gehry, known for his groundbreaking work on the Guggenheim Museum Bilbao. Inaugurated in 1999, this unique building represents a vessel under construction and houses a conference center, concert hall, as well as other facilities like cafes, restaurants, and shopping centers.
name: Palacio Euskalduna
address: Abandoibarra Etorb., 4, Abando, 48011 Bilbao, Bizkaia, Spain

excerpt: This peak features a cablecar to the summit, with a park, restaurants & panoramic city views.
detail_description: Mount Artxanda, located in Bilbao, offers a picturesque setting with breathtaking panoramic views of the cityscape, Nervion River, and surrounding hills. Visitors can reach the summit via a historical funicular known as "funi," providing an exciting journey and one of the best vantage points in the Basque Country. At the top, there are comfortable seating areas and informative displays about the region.
name: Mount Artxanda
address: 48015, Biscay, Spain

detail_description: Bar BIKIAK berri- Bar de Pintxos is a popular spot in Bilbao known for its creative and delicious pintxos, which are small gastronomic treats piled high on the bar. The pintxos are reasonably priced at around 2 each, making it a great place for a traditional and affordable bar crawl experience.
name: Bar BIKIAK berri- Bar de Pintxos
address: Jardines K., 7, Ibaiondo, 48005 Bilbao, Biscay, Spain

detail_description: Cafetería Museo Bellas Artes is a hidden gem in Bilbao, often overshadowed by the Guggenheim. Located in the Dona Casilda Iturrizar park, it offers a mix of classic Spanish and Basque art alongside modern pieces. The café provides a serene setting to enjoy coffee and pastries while overlooking the park or indulge in pintxos and hot sandwiches.
name: Cafetería Museo Bellas Artes
address: Museo Plaza, 2, Abando, 48009 Bilbao, Biscay, Spain

detail_description: Bilbao-Abando station, located in the Abando district of Bilbao, is a bustling terminus for intercity trains. The station's facade, a blend of traditional and modern architecture built in 1870, features a striking stained-glass window depicting Basque culture and iconic landmarks. A colorful stained glass mural designed by Caspar Montes Iturrioz in 1948 adorns the railway level, showcasing scenes from Basque culture, agriculture, and industry.
name: Bilbao-Abando station
address: 48008 Bilbao, BI (Planta 0 y Planta 1, Spain

detail_description: Bilbao City Hall, designed by IMB Arquitectos, is a modern addition to the existing Town Hall. The building features two irregularly angular blocks separated by a wide strip of stairs that also serves as a public plaza space. It houses the technical offices of the Town Hall and offers an inviting atmosphere to the city's residents.
name: Bilbao City Hall
address: Pl. Ernesto Erkoreka, 1, 48007 Bilbao, Vizcaya, Spain

excerpt: Riverside district Indautxu is known for its buzzing nightlife, mixing casual Basque taverns and stylish nightclubs. Cutting-edge exhibition space Azkuna Zentroa occupies landmark wine stores redesigned by Philippe Starck, and the Museum of Fine Arts has works by Velázquez and Goya. Crowds fill Palacio Euskalduna for rock and classical music, and cafe terraces dot nearby waterfront parks.
detail_description: Indautxu, a vibrant district in the riverside area, is renowned for its lively nightlife scene that blends traditional Basque taverns with trendy nightclubs. The Azkuna Zentroa, a cutting-edge exhibition space housed in historic wine stores redesigned by Philippe Starck, and the Museum of Fine Arts showcasing masterpieces by Velázquez and Goya are popular attractions.
name: Indautxu
address: Abando, Bilbao, Biscay, Spain

excerpt: Basque history museum in a 17th-century building with cultural & occupational exhibits.
detail_description: The Museo Arqueológico, Etnográfico e Histórico Vasco is a must-visit for those interested in delving into the origins and history of Basque culture. Housed in a 17th-century building in the heart of the Old Town, this museum is divided into three main departments: Archaeology, Ethnography, and History. Visitors can explore exhibits showcasing Basque cultural and occupational heritage.
name: Museo Arqueológico, Etnográfico e Histórico Vasco
address: Unamuno Miguel Plaza, 4, Ibaiondo, 48006 Bilbao, Bizkaia, Spain

detail_description: Bilbao City Hall, a 19th-century architectural gem, offers a picturesque view from across the river with its French-inspired design featuring three archways and eight pillars. The building's roof boasts an impressive steeple and clock, adding to its imperial charm. Visitors can explore the Old Quarter's medieval streets, admire the Santiago Cathedral from outside, and enjoy a tour of the Guggenheim Museum to see remarkable art pieces.
name: Bilbao City Hall
address: Ernesto Erkoreka Plaza, 12, 48007 Bilbao, Bizkaia, Spain

excerpt: Grand 16th-century church on a hill with mostly Gothic architecture & an ornate gold altarpiece.
detail_description: Begoñako Basilika, also known as the Basilica of Begona, is a 16th-century church located in Bilbao, Spain. It is dedicated to the Virgin of Begona, the patron saint of Biscay. The basilica features mostly Gothic architecture and houses an ornate gold altarpiece.
name: Begoñako Basilika
address: Begoñako Andra Maria Kalea, 38, 48006 Bilbao, Bizkaia, Spain

excerpt: Contemporary Basque cooking & tapas, plus regional wines, in a modern, industrial-chic setup.
detail_description: Gure Toki is a modern, industrial-chic restaurant in Bilbao that offers contemporary Basque cuisine and tapas along with regional wines. The restaurant is known for its crab tempura, salty cod, and tangy goat's cheese in manzanilla sherry. Most of the ingredients used at Gure Toki come from Mercado de la Ribera, which has been a central part of Bilbao's food scene since 1929.
name: Gure Toki
address: Pl. Nueva, 12, Ibaiondo, 48005 Bilbao, Biscay, Spain

detail_description: When visiting Bilbao, don't miss the iconic Artxanda viewpoint. Situated on the Artxanda mountain range, it offers breathtaking panoramic views of the city and surrounding mountains. You can reach the viewpoint by hiking or taking a funicular from the city center. The short 3-minute ride accommodates wheelchairs, bikes, and dogs. Once at the top, you'll find a park and numerous photo opportunities.
name: Artxanda viewpoint
address: Enekuri Artxanda Errepidea, 70, 48015 Bilbao, Bizkaia, Spain

detail_description: Unamuno Miguel Plaza is a charming and historic square located in the heart of Salamanca, Spain. The plaza is named after the renowned Spanish writer and philosopher, Miguel de Unamuno, who was a prominent figure in the city's intellectual and cultural life. Surrounded by beautiful architecture, lively cafes, and bustling street performers, Unamuno Miguel Plaza offers visitors a vibrant atmosphere to soak up the local culture.
name: Unamuno Miguel Plaza
address: Ibaiondo, Bilbao, Bizkaia, Spain

detail_description: The Teatro Campos Elíseos Antzokia, located in Bilbao, is a stunning example of art nouveau architecture. Designed by local architect Alfredo Acebal and French decorator Jean Batiste Darroguy, the theater's exterior features a prominent arch with rich art nouveau decorations. It has become an integral part of Bilbao's cultural scene, offering a blend of classic and modern facilities for various performances.
name: Teatro Campos Elíseos Antzokia
address: C. de Bertendona, 3 bis, 3 bis, Abando, 48008 Bilbao, Bizkaia, Spain

excerpt: Bilbao La Vieja, or “Bilbi,” is a hip district on the Nervión River, with modern fashion boutiques and multicultural bistros in converted industrial buildings. Basque artists exhibit at independent galleries and paint colorful street murals. Nightlife is oriented around craft beer and cocktail bars. Miribilla Park hosts markets and concerts, and the San Luis brick furnace stands as a reminder of local mining history.
detail_description: Bilbao La Vieja, also known as "Bilbi," is a trendy district located on the Nervión River in Bilbao. It's characterized by its modern fashion boutiques, multicultural bistros housed in converted industrial buildings, and vibrant street art created by Basque artists. The neighborhood offers a lively nightlife scene with craft beer and cocktail bars. Miribilla Park hosts markets and concerts while the San Luis brick furnace serves as a reminder of the area's mining history.
name: Bilbao la Vieja
address: Ibaiondo, 48003 Bilbao, Biscay, Spain

excerpt: A 43-foot flower-covered West Highland terrier by Jeff Koons guarding the Guggenheim since 1992.
detail_description: Puppy, a 43-foot floral-covered West Highland terrier sculpture by Jeff Koons, has been standing guard outside the Guggenheim since 1992. The museum is home to a diverse collection of modern and contemporary masterpieces, including large-scale installations like Richard Serra's Snake and Louise Bourgeois' Maman. Inside, visitors can explore Richard Serra's maze-like sculptures and Jenny Holzer's LED columns.
name: Puppy
address: Mazarredo Zumarkalea, 66, Abando, 48009 Bilbao, Bizkaia, Spain

excerpt: Museum with replicas of classical masterpieces from the Louvre, the Vatican & the British Museum.
detail_description: The Museo de Reproducciones Artísticas in Bilbao is a hidden gem that offers a unique experience for art enthusiasts. This museum features replicas of renowned classical masterpieces from prestigious institutions like the Louvre, the Vatican, and the British Museum. It's an ideal family-friendly attraction, allowing visitors to admire famous paintings and sculptures without having to travel extensively. Despite its unassuming surroundings, this museum is truly worth exploring and provides an authentic cultural experience.
name: Bilboko Berreginen Museoa
address: San Frantzisko Kalea, 14, Ibaiondo, 48003 Bilbao, Bizkaia, Spain

detail_description: The Guggenheim is a must-visit for art and architecture enthusiasts. The museum's stunning design by Frank Gehry is a sight to behold, even from the outside. Inside, you can explore a diverse range of artworks, from well-known artists like Picasso and Monet to challenging modern pieces. The museum provides audio devices for self-guided tours, allowing you to delve into the exhibits at your own pace.
name: Guggenheim
address: Abando, 48009 Bilbao, Bizkaia, Spain

detail_description: La Olla de la Plaza Nueva is a stunning neoclassical square located in the heart of Bilbao's old town. Built in the 19th century, it boasts 33 semicircular arches with Doric columns and is surrounded by some of the city's best restaurants and pintxo bars.
name: La Olla de la Plaza Nueva
address: Nueva Plaza, 2, 48005 Bilbao, Bizkaia, Spain

detail_description: Alhondiga aparkalekua, formerly a wine warehouse, is now one of Bilbao's iconic buildings. It offers a variety of activities such as exhibitions and theater performances. The interior features an astonishing space with 100 mismatched columns, creating a unique atmosphere for visitors to enjoy. Additionally, the underground parking lot provides convenient access for vehicles, although the entrance and exit may be slightly narrow.
name: Alhondiga aparkalekua
address: Urkixo Zumarkalea, 43, Abando, 48010 Bilbao, Bizkaia, Spain

detail_description: Las 7 Calles, also known as the Old Quarter of Bilbao, is a historic neighborhood characterized by its seven main streets: Somera, Artecalle, Tenderia, Belosticalle, Carniceria Vieja, Barrencalle and Barrencalle Barrena. This area is renowned for its charming old shops and museums such as the Diocesan Museum of Sacred Art and the Basque Museum.
name: Las 7 Calles
address: Libertate Kalea, 30, Ibaiondo, 48005 Bilbao, Biscay, Spain

detail_description: If you're a food lover eager to explore the rich history of Bilbao, Delight Bilbao Food Tours offers an unforgettable experience with their Historical Walking Tour and Pintxos Dinner. This engaging three-hour journey takes you through the city's historical center, guided by a local expert who will unveil fascinating sights like La Ribera food market and Santiago Cathedral.
name: Delight Bilbao Food Tours
address: Gran Vía de Don Diego López de Haro, 25, Abando, 48009 Bilbao, Bizkaia, Spain

detail_description: Santander, a coastal city, offers a range of activities for visitors. From enjoying the Cantabrian Sea and its stunning coastline to exploring the town's historical heritage and landmarks, there's something for everyone. Nearby Gijon is also worth a visit, offering beautiful beaches and opportunities to explore historical ruins like the Roman Baths and admire Art Nouveau architecture. Visitors have praised the personalized and professional service in Santander, with some even being treated to coffee while they waited.
name: Santander
address: Universidad DE Deusto, Unibertsitate Etorb., 24, Deusto, 48007 Bilbao, Biscay, Spain

detail_description: La Alhóndiga Centro De Ocio Y Cultura S A U is a multifaceted cultural and leisure center located in Bilbao, Basque Country. The surrounding area is renowned for its gastronomy, with Plaza Nueva and its adjacent streets offering an array of bars serving delectable pinchos. Visitors can immerse themselves in the vibrant culinary scene while exploring the bustling bars and family-run restaurants.
name: La Alhóndiga Centro De Ocio Y Cultura S A U
address: Arriquíbar Plaza, 4, Abando, 48008 Bilbao, Biscay, Spain

detail_description: Bilbao is a vibrant city with an impressive street art scene that's sure to captivate visitors, especially teenagers. Iralako Parkea stands out as a colorful and lively space, but the entire city is adorned with striking graffiti and murals. The university area boasts numerous painted murals, while the renowned Brazilian street artist Erb Mon has left his mark throughout Bilbao with his distinctive paint techniques.
name: Street Art
address: San Frantzisko Kalea, 40, Ibaiondo, 48003 Bilbao, Bizkaia, Spain

detail_description: Teatro Arriaga, a stunning architectural gem in Bilbao, draws inspiration from the iconic Paris Opera. Designed by municipal architect Joaquin Rucoba, this magnificent theater opened its doors in 1890 and has since become a cultural landmark.
name: teatro arriaga
address: Abando, 48011 Bilbao, Biscay, Spain

detail_description: Turismo Bulegoa Bilbo Bizkaia is the main tourist information center in Bilbao, Spain. It offers a wide range of resources and support for visitors to explore the city and its surroundings. The knowledgeable staff provides comprehensive services, serving as a gateway to discovering Bilbao's rich cultural heritage, attractions, and activities. Visitors have praised the exceptional attention received at this beautiful tourist office, with helpful and efficient staff providing valuable assistance.
name: Turismo Bulegoa Bilbo Bizkaia
address: Plaza Biribila, 1, Abando, 48001 Bilbao, Bizkaia, Spain

excerpt: Historic marketplace with a wide array of foods including produce, fish, meats, bread & pickles.
detail_description: Erriberako Merkatua, also known as the Ribera Market, is a historic marketplace located in the heart of Bilbao's Old Town. Dating back to the 14th century, this bustling market offers a vibrant selection of locally sourced produce, fish, meats, and other goods. Visitors can immerse themselves in Bilbao's rich culinary traditions while exploring the colorful displays and interacting with lively vendors.
name: Erriberako merkatua
address: Erribera Kalea, s/n, Ibaiondo, 48005 Bilbao, Bizkaia, Spain

excerpt: Historic riverside church of Saint Anthony with a striking bell tower & Gothic features.
detail_description: San Anton eliza, also known as the Church of San Anton, is a historic riverside church located in Bilbao. It features a striking bell tower and Gothic architectural elements. Situated near the Ribera Market and the Nervion river, it offers picturesque views and is easily accessible from various photography spots in the city. Visitors appreciate its location by the estuary and admire its impressive arts, beautiful stained glass windows, and captivating architecture.
name: Antxon Deunaren Eliza
address: Erribera Kalea, 24, Ibaiondo, 48005 Bilbao, Bizkaia, Spain

excerpt: Regional food & grilled meats served in a long-standing locale that has decorative tiles & murals.
detail_description: Café Iruña is a historic café located in Jardines de Albia Square, near the Guggenheim in Bilbao. Built in 1903 by a renowned architect, it has been frequented by famous Basque poets and the writer-philosopher Miguel de Unamuno. The café offers classic Basque dishes such as Bacalao a la koskera and Cordero al txakoli, known for their regional flavors.
name: Café Iruña
address: Colón de Larreátegui K., 13, Abando, 48001 Bilbao, Bizkaia, Spain

excerpt:
Getxo is a town located in the province of Biscay, in the autonomous community of the Basque Country, in Spain.
It is part of Greater Bilbao, and has 75,430 inhabitants. Getxo is mostly an affluent residential area, as well as being the third largest municipality of Biscay. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Getxo, also known as Guecho, is a charming town with around 80,000 residents situated in the province of Biscay within the Basque Country region of Spain. As part of Greater Bilbao, it has become one of the largest municipalities in Biscay. Nestled at the mouth of the Nervion river and boasting beautiful beaches and a bustling maritime port, Getxo has evolved into a popular tourist destination over the past century.
name: Getxo
address: Biscay, Spain

detail_description: Bilbao La Concordia Station, a stunning art nouveau structure adorned with wrought iron and tiles, has been an iconic landmark since its construction in 1902. The station offers convenient access to various destinations and is known for its helpful staff and affordable ticket prices. While lacking amenities such as seating and bathrooms outside the ticketed area, visitors can explore the station's historic charm in the heart of the city. Despite limited facilities, it remains a worthwhile stop for travelers and architecture enthusiasts alike.
name: Bilbao La Concordia Station
address: Bailén Kalea, 2, Abando, 48003 Bilbao, Bizkaia, Spain

name: Iglesia de San José de la Montaña
address: San Jose Plaza, 1, Abando, 48009 Bilbao, Biscay, Spain

detail_description: Bilbao BBK Live is an annual music festival that has been held in Bilbao since 2006. The event takes place in Kobetamendi, offering stunning views of the Arriaz mountains and nearby beaches for relaxation during the day. With a lineup featuring national and international artists from various music genres, including pop, rock, and electronica, the festival attracts thousands of attendees from around the world.
name: Bilbao BBK Live
address: Kobetamendi parkea, Basurtu-Zorrotza, 48002 Bilbao, Bizkaia, Spain

detail_description: The Church of San Francisco de Asis is a serene sanctuary amidst the bustling urban landscape. Constructed in 1890, this magnificent neo-Gothic structure features stunning stained glass windows and intricate stone carvings on its facade. Designed by architect Severino Achucarro, the church's towering spires and pointed arches are truly awe-inspiring. Inside, visitors can admire a beautiful golden Chapel dedicated to El Salvador and an impressive altar.
name: Church of San Francisco de Asís, Bilbao
address: Hurtado de Amezaga Kalea, 21, Abando, 48008 Bilbao, Bizkaia, Spain
